<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-14-0140 </DOCNO><TEXT>Lower costs are available to companies that buy natural gas directly froma producer or supplier rather than from the local utility. A pipelinetransports the natural gas to the utility, who then delivers it to thefacility. Competition is the driving force behind the acceptance of directpurchase by most utilities, pipelines, and producers. The arrangementsare letting the gas industry recapture a substantial number of customerswho had switched to fuel oil and coal. The author explains the conceptsbehind direct purchase, how to determine eligibility, what the advantagesare and how to evaluate the service of the suppliers.</TEXT></DOC>